  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pat the tofu dry, then cut it into small cubes. Heat the sesame oil in a large non-stick pan over a medium-high heat. Add the tofu and cook for 8–10 mins until golden and crisp on all sides."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Grate the garlic and ginger – no need to peel. Slice the roasted red pepper into strips. Finely slice the spring onion and cut the lime into wedges for serving."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a small bowl, whisk together the sriracha, honey, soy sauce, garlic, and ginger with 1-2 tablespoons of water to loosen. Add the yoghurt to a bowl with the kimchi and mix."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour the sauce into the pan with the crispy tofu and toss to coat. Let it bubble for 1–2 minutes until sticky and glossy."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the rice according to the package instructions and add it to a Tupperware container. Top with the honey sriracha tofu, roasted red pepper and kimchi yoghurt."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Sprinkle over the peanuts and spring onion. Once cooled, box up and pop in the fridge, ready for tomorrow’s lunch – they’ll keep for up to 3 days. Serve with a lime wedge for squeezing"
    }
  ],
